      • getElementInfo

        public java.lang.String[] getElementInfo(java.lang.String xpath)
        Retrieve the Element Info, which is made up of:

        1. compBounds (relative to 0,0 of client area?), or ""
        2. calculated SAFS recognition string (not xpath), or ""
        3. the HTML making up the element (parent.innerHTML), or "None"
        4. the innerHTML (if any) of the element itself, or "None"

        Parameters:
        xpath -
        Returns:
